item.title: Philippine Central Bank Keeps Rates Unchanged
item.description: The Philippine central bank left its benchmark rates unchanged, as expected, citing what it said is a moderated outlook for inflation in the Southeast Asian nation.

item.title: EUR/USD's Rebound Has Room to Extend Beyond 1.0945, Charts Show
item.description: EUR/USD’s rebound has room to extend beyond the end-August high of 1.0945, based on technical charts, however, any advance is probably part of a “recovery phase,” and the probability of it breaking above subsequent resistance at 1.1065 seems lower, UOB said.

item.title: Covid's Biggest Economic Winner is Running Out of Steam
item.description: Ireland was one of very few economies to get a boost from the Covid-19 pandemic. Now that unusual dividend is unraveling, in a fresh blow to Europe’s already weakened growth outlook.

item.title: German 10-Year Bund Yields Seen Stabilizing in 2.50%-2.75% Range
item.description: The potential end of rising German bond rates is within view, likely stabilizing between 2.5% and 2.75% [for the 10-year Bund yield], and over time, the driver of lower rates will likely be the trajectory of eurozone core inflation, Neuberger Berman said.

item.title: Lenovo's Profit Falls, But Tops Consensus
item.description: Lenovo Group’s net profit fell 54% in its fiscal second quarter due to a high base in the same period last year when market conditions were more favorable.

item.title: Siemens Sees Slower Revenue Growth
item.description: Siemens said it anticipates a slowdown in revenue growth next year, with global demand for automation products not expected to pick up again until the second half.

item.title: Aegon Lifts Full-Year View
item.description: Aegon raised its 2023 guidance as it reported better-than-expected third-quarter gross operating capital generation on business growth and improved underwriting variances.

item.title: Nikkei Edges 0.3% Lower, Dragged by Consumer-Related Stocks
item.description: Japan’s Nikkei Stock Average edged 0.3% lower to close at 33424.41, dragged by consumer-related stocks.

item.title: China Pledges to Attract More Foreign Investment, Boost Consumption
item.description: China’s state planner said it would step up efforts to attract foreign investment and improve domestic consumption, as Beijing moved to provide more support for the economy.

item.title: Global Fight Against Inflation Turns a Corner
item.description: Falling inflation across industrialized countries opens the door for central banks to start cutting interest rates next year.
